        <section id="introduction">
            <h2>1. Platform Overview</h2>
            <p>**Vidyari** is a **community-driven digital asset management platform** engineered for the secure distribution and retrieval of various digital resources across academic, professional, and creative domains. The platform supports monetization, resource verification, and advanced discoverability through AI integration.</p>

            <h3>1.1 Supported Digital Assets</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>**Academic/Educational:** Research papers, university documents, syllabi, and video lectures.</li>
                <li>**Professional/Software:** eBooks, technical guides, source code snippets, standalone applications, and software plugins.</li>
                <li>**General Utilities:** Design templates, high-fidelity media files, and supplementary learning material.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>1.2 Core Capabilities</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>**Content Management:** Multi-format file uploading and dashboard-based content lifecycle control.</li>
                <li>**Monetization:** Configuration of paid assets utilizing secure payment gateways and **coupon code** functionality.</li>
                <li>**User Experience:** Intuitive dashboards for tracking activity, earnings, and download history.</li>
            <li>**Platform Administration:** Dedicated Admin Panel for comprehensive user, content, and payment monitoring.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <hr>

        <section id="user-guide">
            <h2>2. User Operations Guide</h2>

            <h3 id="account-management">2.1 Account and Security Management</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>**Registration:** Accounts can be provisioned using **Email/Password** or via integrated **Google OAuth** for expedited access.</li>
                <li>**Authentication:** Standardized login/logout procedures.</li>
                <li>**Security:** **Password Reset** is facilitated via a secure, time-sensitive link delivered to the registered email address.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="uploading-files">2.2 Content Submission Lifecycle</h3>
            <p>The content submission process is structured into three mandatory stages to ensure comprehensive metadata capture and successful hosting.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>**Supported Formats:** PDF, DOCX, PPTX, EPUB, EXE, ZIP/RAR, MP4, JPEG, PNG, and other common formats.</li>
                <li>**Capacity Limit:** Content files must not exceed **7GB** per individual upload instance.</li>
                <li>**Submission Stages:**
                    <ol>
                        <li>**Configuration:** Select the asset file, define the **Title, Description, Category, Tags**, and set pricing parameters (if applicable).</li>
                        <li>**Verification:** Review the content preview, confirm metadata accuracy, and configure auxiliary settings (e.g., licensing, visibility).</li>
                        <li>**Deployment:** Execute the **Submit** action. The content is then queued for processing and immediate availability (or moderation).</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tip">
                **Metadata Requirement:** Accurate, detailed metadata (**Title, Tags, Category**) is critical for **Search Engine Optimization (SEO)** and **AI-driven discoverability**.
            </div>

            <h3 id="browsing-downloading">2.3 Content Retrieval (Downloads)</h3>
            <p>This section outlines procedures for accessing and downloading content, distinguishing between free and paid assets.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>**Search Functionality:** The system supports advanced search queries utilizing keywords, content type, creator identity, and specific content **tags**.</li>
                <li>**Content Organization:** Resources are hierarchically classified under major categories: Academic, eBooks, Software, Media, and Templates.</li>
                <li>**Pre-acquisition Review:** A secure, embedded **Preview** function is provided for specific file types (e.g., PDF) prior to download or purchase commitment.</li>
                <li>**Acquisition (Free):** The **Download** action initiates the file transfer for free assets. Users retain permanent access via their Download History in the Dashboard.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="payments">2.4 Transaction Procedures (Purchases)</h3>
            <p>This covers the acquisition process for monetized content, including payment methods and policy for successful purchase and asset access.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>**Accepted Methods:** Support for secure transactions via **UPI, major Credit/Debit Cards, Net Banking,** and digital wallet services.</li>
                <li>**Transaction Flow (Purchase):**
                    <ol>
                        <li>Select the target asset and initiate **Buy Now**.</li>
                        <li>Input or apply a valid **Coupon Code** (if available) to adjust the price.</li>
                        <li>Complete payment via the designated secure gateway.</li>
                        <li>Confirmation initiates immediate and permanent activation of the asset download link within the user dashboard's Purchase History.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>**Refund Policy:** Requests are processed exclusively for failed payment transactions or confirmed unavailability of the acquired asset. Users must provide the **Transaction ID** for verification.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="chat-feature">2.5 Communication: Chat Feature</h3>
            <p>Vidyari includes an integrated messaging system to facilitate direct, contextual communication between users and content creators (or other users, depending on settings).</p>
            <ul>
                <li>**Access:** The chat interface is accessible from the user's Dashboard or directly via a dedicated icon on the Creator's public profile page or the content detail page.</li>
                <li>**Purpose:** Primarily intended for pre-sales questions, technical clarification on content usage, or reporting minor content discrepancies directly to the source.</li>
                <li>**Messaging Integrity:** All conversations are logged and subject to platform **Content and Behavior Policies**. Any attempt to facilitate transactions outside the official payment gateway is a violation and subject to disciplinary action.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="note">
                **Support Channel:** The in-app chat is strictly for peer-to-peer communication. For official technical support, account issues, or payment failures, users must utilize the dedicated **Contact Support** (Section 6) email channel.
            </div>
        </section>

